[
    {
        "text": "Can we say advices?",
        "start": 0.24,
        "duration": 2.465
    },
    {
        "text": "Feedbacks?",
        "start": 2.705,
        "duration": 1.533
    },
    {
        "text": "Softwares?",
        "start": 4.238,
        "duration": 1.705
    },
    {
        "text": "The answer may surprise you.",
        "start": 5.943,
        "duration": 1.982
    },
    {
        "text": "By the end of the lesson, you will have learned how to use common words, like these, correctly.",
        "start": 7.925,
        "duration": 5.611
    },
    {
        "text": "Hello and welcome everyone, this is Minoo at Anglo-Link.",
        "start": 13.536,
        "duration": 3.504
    },
    {
        "text": "Remember that there are lots of free exercises for you to enjoy \non my online course.",
        "start": 17.04,
        "duration": 5.242
    },
    {
        "text": "You can access them by creating a free account on my website:",
        "start": 22.282,
        "duration": 4.278
    },
    {
        "text": "Anglo-Link.com.",
        "start": 26.56,
        "duration": 1.757
    },
    {
        "text": "The link to set up your account is in the description box.",
        "start": 28.317,
        "duration": 3.843
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay! Let's start by reminding ourselves what the difference is between",
        "start": 32.16,
        "duration": 5.139
    },
    {
        "text": " a countable noun and an uncountable noun.",
        "start": 37.299,
        "duration": 4.128
    },
    {
        "text": "A countable noun is, believe it or not,",
        "start": 42.56,
        "duration": 2.988
    },
    {
        "text": " a noun you can count.",
        "start": 45.548,
        "duration": 2.185
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, take the word 'fact'.",
        "start": 48.526,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "You can say:",
        "start": 51.969,
        "duration": 1.488
    },
    {
        "text": "A fact.",
        "start": 53.457,
        "duration": 1.238
    },
    {
        "text": "And: two facts.",
        "start": 54.695,
        "duration": 2.553
    },
    {
        "text": "So, obviously, an uncountable noun is a noun you cannot count.",
        "start": 58.656,
        "duration": 4.781
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, take the word 'information'.",
        "start": 64.64,
        "duration": 2.899
    },
    {
        "text": "It is similar to fact,",
        "start": 67.539,
        "duration": 1.981
    },
    {
        "text": "but for some reason, 'information' is uncountable.",
        "start": 69.52,
        "duration": 4.155
    },
    {
        "text": "Don't ask me why. English is not a logical language.",
        "start": 73.675,
        "duration": 4.415
    },
    {
        "text": "So, you cannot say:",
        "start": 78.09,
        "duration": 1.91
    },
    {
        "text": "An information.",
        "start": 80.0,
        "duration": 1.618
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 83.285,
        "duration": 0.727
    },
    {
        "text": "Two informations.",
        "start": 84.012,
        "duration": 1.742
    },
    {
        "text": "If you want to count these words, you have to pair \nthem with a countable noun.",
        "start": 88.172,
        "duration": 5.484
    },
    {
        "text": "A very common word is 'piece'.",
        "start": 94.08,
        "duration": 2.738
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, you can say:",
        "start": 96.818,
        "duration": 2.169
    },
    {
        "text": "A piece of information.",
        "start": 98.987,
        "duration": 1.718
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 100.705,
        "duration": 0.985
    },
    {
        "text": "Two pieces of information.",
        "start": 101.69,
        "duration": 3.175
    },
    {
        "text": "Unfortunately, there is no logic or rule that \ncan help you to know if a word is countable or uncountable.",
        "start": 106.068,
        "duration": 7.088
    },
    {
        "text": "The only way to learn these is practice.",
        "start": 113.156,
        "duration": 3.044
    },
    {
        "text": "So, I've put a little quiz together to \nhelp you practice some of these words.",
        "start": 116.2,
        "duration": 4.599
    },
    {
        "text": "I've chosen 10 words, and I'm going to give you three seconds to decide whether each word is countable or uncountable.",
        "start": 120.799,
        "duration": 7.711
    },
    {
        "text": "So, when you're ready, let's begin our quiz with the first word which is...",
        "start": 128.84,
        "duration": 4.735
    },
    {
        "text": "Suggestion!",
        "start": 134.48,
        "duration": 1.197
    },
    {
        "text": "Is that countable or uncountable?",
        "start": 135.677,
        "duration": 3.323
    },
    {
        "text": "It's countable!",
        "start": 142.64,
        "duration": 1.67
    },
    {
        "text": "So, you can say:",
        "start": 144.31,
        "duration": 1.784
    },
    {
        "text": "A suggestion.",
        "start": 146.094,
        "duration": 1.059
    },
    {
        "text": "And you can say:",
        "start": 147.153,
        "duration": 1.217
    },
    {
        "text": "Suggestions.",
        "start": 148.37,
        "duration": 1.07
    },
    {
        "text": "For example:",
        "start": 149.44,
        "duration": 1.363
    },
    {
        "text": "That's a great suggestion.",
        "start": 150.803,
        "duration": 1.736
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 152.539,
        "duration": 1.077
    },
    {
        "text": "Can I make a few suggestions?",
        "start": 153.616,
        "duration": 2.443
    },
    {
        "text": "The next word is 'advice'.",
        "start": 156.64,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Is it countable or uncountable?",
        "start": 159.14,
        "duration": 3.717
    },
    {
        "text": "Advice is...",
        "start": 165.513,
        "duration": 1.528
    },
    {
        "text": "Uncountable.",
        "start": 167.041,
        "duration": 1.383
    },
    {
        "text": "Therefore, you cannot say:",
        "start": 168.424,
        "duration": 2.461
    },
    {
        "text": "An advice.",
        "start": 170.885,
        "duration": 0.998
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 171.883,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Advices.",
        "start": 172.383,
        "duration": 1.207
    },
    {
        "text": "You have to use it as a collective noun.",
        "start": 173.59,
        "duration": 2.222
    },
    {
        "text": "For example:",
        "start": 175.812,
        "duration": 0.906
    },
    {
        "text": "She needed some advice.",
        "start": 176.718,
        "duration": 2.179
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, if you want to count advice, you need to \npair it with a word that is countable.",
        "start": 179.248,
        "duration": 6.492
    },
    {
        "text": "A very common word in this situation is 'piece'.",
        "start": 185.925,
        "duration": 3.866
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, you can say:",
        "start": 189.791,
        "duration": 1.886
    },
    {
        "text": "He gave me a good piece of advice.",
        "start": 191.677,
        "duration": 2.825
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 194.502,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "I have two pieces of advice for you.",
        "start": 195.002,
        "duration": 3.323
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay! The next word is 'feedback'.",
        "start": 198.96,
        "duration": 3.146
    },
    {
        "text": "Is it countable or uncountable?",
        "start": 202.106,
        "duration": 2.683
    },
    {
        "text": "What do you think?",
        "start": 204.789,
        "duration": 1.779
    },
    {
        "text": "It is uncountable.",
        "start": 210.16,
        "duration": 2.126
    },
    {
        "text": "Many of you think that 'feedback' is countable. But, it isn't.",
        "start": 212.913,
        "duration": 3.809
    },
    {
        "text": "Be careful!",
        "start": 216.722,
        "duration": 0.878
    },
    {
        "text": "You cannot say:",
        "start": 217.6,
        "duration": 1.264
    },
    {
        "text": "A feedback.",
        "start": 218.864,
        "duration": 0.914
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 219.778,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Feedbacks.",
        "start": 220.278,
        "duration": 0.949
    },
    {
        "text": "We always use this as a collective noun.",
        "start": 221.227,
        "duration": 3.173
    },
    {
        "text": "And we don't even have another word, a countable \nword that can pair up with it.",
        "start": 224.4,
        "duration": 5.49
    },
    {
        "text": "So, just use it on its own. You can say:",
        "start": 229.89,
        "duration": 3.804
    },
    {
        "text": "Let me give you some feedback.",
        "start": 233.694,
        "duration": 2.05
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 235.744,
        "duration": 0.819
    },
    {
        "text": "Thank you for your valuable feedback.",
        "start": 236.563,
        "duration": 3.065
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay! The next word is 'news'.",
        "start": 240.148,
        "duration": 3.697
    },
    {
        "text": "Is it countable or uncountable?",
        "start": 243.845,
        "duration": 2.825
    },
    {
        "text": "'News' is...",
        "start": 250.56,
        "duration": 1.1
    },
    {
        "text": "Uncountable!",
        "start": 251.66,
        "duration": 1.328
    },
    {
        "text": "You cannot say:",
        "start": 253.339,
        "duration": 1.31
    },
    {
        "text": "A news.",
        "start": 254.649,
        "duration": 1.255
    },
    {
        "text": "So, don't say:",
        "start": 255.904,
        "duration": 1.631
    },
    {
        "text": "That's a great news.",
        "start": 257.535,
        "duration": 1.81
    },
    {
        "text": "Just say:",
        "start": 259.345,
        "duration": 1.133
    },
    {
        "text": "That's great news.",
        "start": 260.478,
        "duration": 2.032
    },
    {
        "text": "You can pair news up with piece.",
        "start": 262.51,
        "duration": 3.257
    },
    {
        "text": "You can say:",
        "start": 265.767,
        "duration": 1.201
    },
    {
        "text": "That's a great piece of news.",
        "start": 266.968,
        "duration": 2.253
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, be careful that when we talk about news on \nthe media, like on television or in the newspaper,",
        "start": 269.68,
        "duration": 7.249
    },
    {
        "text": "we don't say 'piece' we use the word 'item'.",
        "start": 276.929,
        "duration": 4.131
    },
    {
        "text": "An item of news. Or a news item.",
        "start": 281.06,
        "duration": 3.55
    },
    {
        "text": "The next word is...",
        "start": 285.28,
        "duration": 1.537
    },
    {
        "text": "'series'.",
        "start": 286.817,
        "duration": 1.053
    },
    {
        "text": "That's a tricky one.",
        "start": 287.87,
        "duration": 1.447
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you think it's countable or uncountable?",
        "start": 289.317,
        "duration": 3.495
    },
    {
        "text": "It's actually both.",
        "start": 296.08,
        "duration": 1.965
    },
    {
        "text": " You can put 'a' with it. Say:",
        "start": 298.045,
        "duration": 2.35
    },
    {
        "text": "A series.",
        "start": 300.395,
        "duration": 1.164
    },
    {
        "text": "But, you can't make it plural. You can't say: serieses.",
        "start": 301.559,
        "duration": 4.375
    },
    {
        "text": "So, the word 'series' is both singular and plural.",
        "start": 305.934,
        "duration": 4.066
    },
    {
        "text": "You can say:",
        "start": 310.0,
        "duration": 1.203
    },
    {
        "text": "This is an interesting series.",
        "start": 311.203,
        "duration": 2.308
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 313.511,
        "duration": 0.98
    },
    {
        "text": "There are very few good series on television.",
        "start": 314.491,
        "duration": 4.104
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay! Let's look at coffee and tea.",
        "start": 319.481,
        "duration": 3.61
    },
    {
        "text": "Are they countable or uncountable?",
        "start": 323.276,
        "duration": 3.181
    },
    {
        "text": "They're both as well.",
        "start": 330.24,
        "duration": 1.547
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's look at them in their uncountable form.",
        "start": 331.787,
        "duration": 3.434
    },
    {
        "text": "In general, you would say:",
        "start": 335.221,
        "duration": 2.139
    },
    {
        "text": "I like black coffee.",
        "start": 337.36,
        "duration": 1.948
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 339.308,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Green tea is my favourite drink.",
        "start": 339.808,
        "duration": 2.628
    },
    {
        "text": "But, they can also be countable when you go to order some.",
        "start": 342.657,
        "duration": 4.947
    },
    {
        "text": "Most people, instead of saying:",
        "start": 348.046,
        "duration": 1.772
    },
    {
        "text": "I'd like a cup of black coffee please.",
        "start": 349.818,
        "duration": 3.102
    },
    {
        "text": "Just say:",
        "start": 352.92,
        "duration": 0.939
    },
    {
        "text": "I'd like a black coffee please.",
        "start": 353.859,
        "duration": 2.513
    },
    {
        "text": "Or instead of saying:",
        "start": 356.372,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Could we have two cups of green tea please.",
        "start": 358.372,
        "duration": 3.308
    },
    {
        "text": "They just say:",
        "start": 361.68,
        "duration": 1.223
    },
    {
        "text": "We'll have two green teas please.",
        "start": 362.903,
        "duration": 2.593
    },
    {
        "text": "So, they can be countable or uncountable.",
        "start": 365.496,
        "duration": 3.993
    },
    {
        "text": "Right! Let's look at 'software' and 'hardware'.",
        "start": 370.431,
        "duration": 3.947
    },
    {
        "text": "What do you think? Are they countable or uncountable?",
        "start": 374.692,
        "duration": 3.642
    },
    {
        "text": "They're definitely uncountable.",
        "start": 382.08,
        "duration": 2.55
    },
    {
        "text": "Avoid saying:",
        "start": 384.63,
        "duration": 1.336
    },
    {
        "text": "A software.",
        "start": 385.966,
        "duration": 0.869
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 386.835,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Softwares.",
        "start": 387.335,
        "duration": 0.893
    },
    {
        "text": "You may hear that, but it's not correct.",
        "start": 388.228,
        "duration": 2.733
    },
    {
        "text": "Use them as collective nouns. For example:",
        "start": 391.219,
        "duration": 2.936
    },
    {
        "text": "We need new software.",
        "start": 394.155,
        "duration": 2.03
    },
    {
        "text": "Or, you can  pair them up with countable words like:",
        "start": 396.185,
        "duration": 3.667
    },
    {
        "text": "We need a new software package.",
        "start": 399.852,
        "duration": 2.991
    },
    {
        "text": "Or, use the word piece again.",
        "start": 402.843,
        "duration": 2.028
    },
    {
        "text": "You can pair these two words up with peace. \nFor example:",
        "start": 404.871,
        "duration": 3.912
    },
    {
        "text": "These are great pieces of hardware.",
        "start": 408.783,
        "duration": 2.936
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay! Number 8 is...",
        "start": 412.96,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "'equipment'.",
        "start": 415.0,
        "duration": 1.122
    },
    {
        "text": "Countable or uncountable?",
        "start": 416.417,
        "duration": 2.535
    },
    {
        "text": "Equipment is also uncountable.",
        "start": 423.04,
        "duration": 2.864
    },
    {
        "text": "So, avoid saying:",
        "start": 425.904,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "An equipment. Or: Equipments.",
        "start": 427.424,
        "duration": 1.889
    },
    {
        "text": "Use it in general:",
        "start": 429.313,
        "duration": 1.407
    },
    {
        "text": "This is very old equipment.",
        "start": 430.72,
        "duration": 2.329
    },
    {
        "text": "Or, pair it up with 'piece'.",
        "start": 433.049,
        "duration": 2.198
    },
    {
        "text": "For example:",
        "start": 435.247,
        "duration": 0.832
    },
    {
        "text": "This printer is a very old piece of equipment.",
        "start": 436.079,
        "duration": 3.735
    },
    {
        "text": "Right! The next word is...",
        "start": 440.663,
        "duration": 2.166
    },
    {
        "text": "'research'.",
        "start": 442.829,
        "duration": 1.094
    },
    {
        "text": "Countable or uncountable?",
        "start": 443.923,
        "duration": 2.793
    },
    {
        "text": "It can be both.",
        "start": 450.689,
        "duration": 1.819
    },
    {
        "text": "In British English, interestingly, it can be countable:",
        "start": 452.508,
        "duration": 4.583
    },
    {
        "text": "Researches.",
        "start": 457.091,
        "duration": 1.336
    },
    {
        "text": "But, it sounds so much like 'researchers' which,\n is the people who do research,",
        "start": 458.427,
        "duration": 6.977
    },
    {
        "text": "that I would recommend you avoid using it as a countable noun.",
        "start": 465.404,
        "duration": 4.506
    },
    {
        "text": "Use it as an uncountable noun.",
        "start": 469.91,
        "duration": 2.424
    },
    {
        "text": "You can pair it up with 'piece':",
        "start": 472.334,
        "duration": 1.986
    },
    {
        "text": "A piece of research.",
        "start": 474.32,
        "duration": 1.689
    },
    {
        "text": "Or, you can say:",
        "start": 476.009,
        "duration": 1.091
    },
    {
        "text": "A research paper.",
        "start": 477.1,
        "duration": 1.349
    },
    {
        "text": "Or, you use the synonym:",
        "start": 478.449,
        "duration": 2.437
    },
    {
        "text": "A study.",
        "start": 480.886,
        "duration": 1.275
    },
    {
        "text": "And finally, our last word is...",
        "start": 482.8,
        "duration": 2.859
    },
    {
        "text": "'knowledge'.",
        "start": 485.659,
        "duration": 0.943
    },
    {
        "text": "Is it countable or uncountable?",
        "start": 486.602,
        "duration": 3.157
    },
    {
        "text": "That's a tricky one as well.",
        "start": 493.2,
        "duration": 1.634
    },
    {
        "text": "It can be both.",
        "start": 494.834,
        "duration": 1.626
    },
    {
        "text": "It can be countable or uncountable.",
        "start": 496.46,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, generally we never say:",
        "start": 499.34,
        "duration": 2.238
    },
    {
        "text": "A knowledge.",
        "start": 501.578,
        "duration": 0.943
    },
    {
        "text": " Or: Knowledges.",
        "start": 502.521,
        "duration": 1.275
    },
    {
        "text": "So, we use the expression, for example:",
        "start": 503.796,
        "duration": 2.166
    },
    {
        "text": "To my knowledge.",
        "start": 505.962,
        "duration": 1.534
    },
    {
        "text": "But, with an adjective, it suddenly becomes countable.",
        "start": 507.76,
        "duration": 4.191
    },
    {
        "text": "So, you would say:",
        "start": 511.951,
        "duration": 1.062
    },
    {
        "text": " I have a basic knowledge of german.",
        "start": 513.013,
        "duration": 3.033
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 516.046,
        "duration": 0.616
    },
    {
        "text": "She has a good knowledge of history.",
        "start": 516.662,
        "duration": 3.181
    },
    {
        "text": "Right! That's all for today.",
        "start": 520.88,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "You'll find lots more tips on correct language usage in this playlist.",
        "start": 523.04,
        "duration": 5.137
    },
    {
        "text": " And remember to check my online course at\n Anglo-Link.com",
        "start": 528.177,
        "duration": 4.143
    },
    {
        "text": "for lots more free lessons and exercises.",
        "start": 532.32,
        "duration": 3.319
    },
    {
        "text": "And don't forget to subscribe, like, and comment.",
        "start": 535.639,
        "duration": 4.084
